Finally got my SparkCore, an Arduino built with on-board WiFi (no need for a Arduino WiFi shield). This version is a different take on the &ldquo;Internet of Things&rdquo; and &ldquo;Build internet-connected hardware&rdquo;
Here&rsquo;s a picture of the Spark connected to the WiFi running my first HelloWorld app downloaded directly from the Spark IDE to the core.
Looking forward to building some designs around it! To learn more about Arduino and SparkCore visit their corresponding sites.

Today I&rsquo;ll comment on a commonly overlooked feature now available in Java (since Java 5.0) called &ldquo;varargs&rdquo;.
How many times have you done this?
[sourcecode language=&ldquo;jscript&rdquo;]
public ConstructorOne(String personFullName){ // Does something }
//and later on added another constructor that took another parameter
public ConstructorOne(String personFirstName, String personLastName){ // Now breaks down the name to pass along two strings instead of one. }
// and so on&hellip;
[/sourcecode]
Well, not anymore.
